# genomedk-jobs skill — per-project config.
#
# Copy this to `hpc.env` (or `.hpc/hpc.env`) at your PROJECT root and fill in.
# The wrappers walk up from the current directory to find it, so it is found
# from anywhere inside the project. Shell-sourceable (KEY=value, no spaces
# around `=`). No secrets live here, so it is safe to commit and share with
# collaborators on the same project.

# --- cluster identity ---------------------------------------------------

# SSH alias for the login node, defined in ~/.ssh/config with
# ControlMaster/ControlPersist. See reference/ssh_setup.md.
HPC_HOST=genomedk

# Your username on the cluster (used to filter `squeue`).
HPC_USER=your-cluster-username

# SLURM account to charge.
HPC_ACCOUNT=your_slurm_account

# --- the write boundary -------------------------------------------------

# THE most important setting. Every remote write (push, submit, fetch) is
# refused unless it lands under this directory. Must be an absolute path you
# own on the shared filesystem. On GenomeDK these live under
# /faststorage/project/<PROJECT>/...
HPC_REMOTE_ROOT=/faststorage/project/YOUR_PROJECT/you/your-subdir

# --- defaults (override per-job on the command line) --------------------

# Default SLURM partition. A single name (normal) or a comma-list
# (gpu-short,gpu-l40s) so SLURM picks the first free one; the walltime cap is
# then the most restrictive partition in the list. `normal` is GenomeDK's
# default CPU partition. For a GPU job, set a GPU partition here AND pass
# `--gpus N` to hpc_submit.py (it requests 0 GPUs by default). GenomeDK GPU
# partitions: gpu-l40s / gpu-short (L40S, 48 GB) and gpu-h200 (H200, 141 GB).
# Run `gnodes` on the login node for the live list. Docs: https://genome.au.dk/docs/
HPC_PARTITION=normal

# Email for SLURM END/FAIL notifications. Leave blank to disable mail.
HPC_MAIL_USER=you@example.com

# Subdirectory under HPC_REMOTE_ROOT that holds your pushed code and is the
# working directory for jobs.
HPC_CODE_SUBDIR=repo

# What `hpc_push.sh` (called with no arguments) syncs up, space-separated,
# relative to the project root. Include your environment lockfile here: the
# skill assumes pixi (pixi.toml + pixi.lock), installed on the login node and
# run via `pixi run` — see the Dependencies section in SKILL.md. Swap these for
# environment.yml / requirements.txt if you use conda / pip instead.
HPC_PUSH_PATHS="src scripts pixi.toml pixi.lock"

# Shell lines injected into every job before your command runs (environment
# activation, caches, etc.). They run inside the job, where $REMOTE_ROOT is
# already defined, so reference $REMOTE_ROOT (not $HPC_REMOTE_ROOT). Use SINGLE
# quotes so $REMOTE_ROOT/$HOME are expanded inside the job rather than when this
# file is sourced (double quotes would expand $REMOTE_ROOT to empty here).
# Example for pixi on GenomeDK:
# HPC_JOB_SETUP='export PIXI_CACHE_DIR=$REMOTE_ROOT/.pixi-cache; export PATH=$HOME/.pixi/bin:$PATH; export TORCH_HOME=$REMOTE_ROOT/.torch-cache'

# --- local bookkeeping --------------------------------------------------

# Project root on your machine. Defaults to the directory containing hpc.env.
# HPC_LOCAL_ROOT=.

# Where the JSONL audit trail is written locally. Defaults to
# $HPC_LOCAL_ROOT/.hpc_audit.log.
# HPC_AUDIT_LOG=.hpc_audit.log

# --- safety toggles (usually leave unset) -------------------------------

# Set to 1 to keep a recoverable copy of any remote file a push overwrites,
# under $HPC_REMOTE_ROOT/.hpc_backups/<timestamp>. Push never deletes either way.
# HPC_PUSH_BACKUP=1

# The first push/submit verifies over SSH that HPC_REMOTE_ROOT is owned by you,
# to catch a mistyped path pointing at another project. Set to 1 only if the
# root is a genuinely shared directory you do not own.
# HPC_ALLOW_UNOWNED_ROOT=1
